Postpone Arctic Monkeys gig in Glasgow because of the illness Alex Turners
The rock band Arctic Monkeys has postponed a gig in Glasgow, after their lead singer is diagnosed with laryngeal inflammation.
The band from Sheffield should play on Friday in the Hydro.
Due to the illness of the lead singer Alex Turner's concert, however, must now be moved.
The announcement came out of the band, having previously had to postpone an appearance at the LG Arena in Birmingham on Thursday.
In a statement on their official website, the Arctic Monkeys: "following the decision to cancel the show in the LG Arena in Birmingham this evening and on medical advice, the Arctic Monkeys must also cancel the show at the Hydro in Glasgow on Friday 1 November."
"Alex Turner was diagnosed with a throat inflammation, which is why he does not, unfortunately, can occur."
The show at the LG Arena in Birmingham will now take place on 20 November, which was moved to the 21 November at the Hydro in Glasgow.
